ce:section.ce:para:
In the present wick flow condensation model, the topology of the wick structure is provided as an input. The wick topology defines the local pore size distribution (i.e., wick and gap regions), the local enhanced surface area, and the local porosity of the wick structure. As the model computes the condensate film thickness, the local void fraction is calculated. The only unknown parameter of the present semi-analytical flow condensation model is the effective wick-condensate thermal conductivity, which is determined by fitting to the experimental data. In summary, the wick flow condensation model developed in the current study estimates (a) the local heat flux (

